description:
This is the old time sly British wit in fine form. You must see this one.  The opening 10 minutes is priceless.  They slipped a bunch of lines and situations past the British censors of the time.  The one I still think is the funniest is when the narrator is describing the little town.  He gets to a point where he says they are a simple people with simple pleasures.  And about 12 kids come running out the door to play. LOL.


